USA: Repetition is the mother of wisdom
It is comical that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats on the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the most foolish.
When he finally revealed his eagerly awaited Afghan approach, it was shown to be a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only is the phrase &quot;as in Iraq&quot; used multiple times in the same text, but he also did not hesitate to use the title of Bush&#39;s January 2007 statement for his own statement: &quot;A new way forward.&quot;
It was he himself who three years ago criticized Bush&#39;s idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from the civil war. And that he criticized as &quot;an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences.&quot;
The following months, however, demonstrated that Bush&#39;s strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful one, so that today there is nothing in the news about Iraq.
Bush&#39;s reputation did not improve, yet objectively he left his successor in a much more favorable starting position than might have been expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes the miracle will be repeated.
The field captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghan operation General Stanley McCristal. He, even despite traditional subordinate relationships, subjected indecisive riflemen in the White House to harsh criticism.
He asked for 40,000 men to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but could not think of anything better, so at least he deceived the general about 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he himself previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic of the entire Obama strategy seems to be his goal, to begin withdrawing troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and to complete this procedure in three years. The entire Obama doctrine generated more questions than the answers it offered.
Many doubt that the increase will bear the same fruit as the Iraq procedure.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is honored.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing their chief every day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a Potemkin people. Behind him will remain patriarchal tribal relations.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily difficult due to the confused relationships, further complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even setting a state that is &quot;capable of action&quot;, a minimal goal of the entire operation, doesn&#39;t seem very real.
The horizon of Obama&#39;s strategy collides with his voluntarism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to deteriorate and is now on the verge of exploding.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing of reality, can believe that the military sent to war to &quot;come home soon&quot; will perform some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date for the withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, as the Taliban will see it as an indirect declaration of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans are less and less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, and do not want to explain to their constituents, what connection the security of Germany or Italy has to the war with the Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and the increased sanctions have no effect on the Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek the answers precisely when, according to Obama, America begins the triumphant withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
However, each such solution will spell a dramatic setback for the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that the presidential elections are three years away and that is why there is still a long time to find another strategy, if it turns out to be a total failure.
Goldman Sachs bank executives will no longer receive cash bonuses
The top executives of the US bank Goldman Sachs will not receive the cash bonuses this year.
The entity announced it to react to the harsh criticism of its salary practices.
The group of 30 senior managers will receive, instead of money, shares that cannot be sold for a minimum period of five years.
In addition, the shares may be withdrawn in the event that they have assumed excessive risks.
According to Reuters, Goldman Sachs thus became the leader in the effort to unite bonuses on Wall Street with long-term power.
I suppose Wall Street is fully aware of the longer path it has to take, said former JPMorgan bank investor Douglas Elliott.
The problem is in the details, he added.
Goldman Sachs bank faced criticism after setting aside nearly $ 17 billion (nearly CZK 300 billion) for bonuses in the first three quarters of this year.
The total sum of bonuses in the entity for this year, according to Reuters, will probably exceed, despite the measure announced today, 20,000 million dollars.
The high bonuses in the banking sector became, with the arrival of the financial crisis, a sensitive issue in politics.
Britain announced on Wednesday that it plans to levy a 50% tax on bank bonuses in excess of £ 25,000 (approximately CZK 712,000) in one fell swoop.
France is also preparing similar measures.
This year women received Nobel Prizes in all categories except Physics
Five women, which is a record number, received this year&#39;s Nobel Prizes from King Charles XVI Gustav of Sweden in Stockholm today, in specialized categories and in literature.
In addition to the four scientists, a German writer of Romanian origin, Herta Müller, also appeared among the winners.
The Nobel Prize in medicine was received by two American biologists, Elizabeth Blackburn and Carol Greider, as well as their compatriot Jack Szostak for research in the field of chromosomes.
The Nobel Prize in chemistry was received by the Israeli Ada Jonath and the Americans Venkatraman Ramakrishna and Thomas Steitz for the explanation of the structure and function of ribosomes.
The last prize awarded, the Nobel Prize in Economics, was received by the American Elinor Ostrom and her compatriot Oliver Williamson for the analysis of an economic report.
The only specialized category, without an award-winning woman, was Physics.
This award was received today by scientists Charles Kao for research in the field of optical cables, and George Smith with Willard Boyle for the invention of the CCD chip, which is the basis of all digital cameras, faxes or telescopes.
Each winner collected the diploma, the Nobel medal and the certificate of the money received.
This sum in each category is up to SEK 10 million (approximately CZK 25 million).
In the case of having several winners in each category, the prize is distributed among themselves.
The traditionally most anticipated Nobel, that of Peace, was received this afternoon in Oslo, Norway, by US President Barack Obama.
