Winning the UEFA Champions League doesn&#39;t just bring glory. It is also one of the main sources of income for the big clubs.
So much so, that the competition has distributed 5,362.5 million euros to the 105 teams (12 of them Spanish) that have participated in the event since the tournament was created in the 1992/1993 season, according to UEFA data.
Real Madrid and FC Barcelona have come out of this cast well.
The white club was the third on the continent to earn the most money for participating, and the only one, together with AC Milan, to have won the trophy three times.
The Catalan, the current champion and the last winner of the extinct European Cup in 1992, is fifth in the standings.
The list is led by Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams that also made the most money for participating in the last Champions League.
