New tools for car appraisal
In these days of storms and accidents, it&#39;s not just car workshops that win.
Every day thousands of cars that have suffered an accident are towed to a workshop, where an expert must assess the damage suffered and what the repair cost will be.
No claim is the same, and calculating parts costs and labor time can be time consuming and complicated.
Manually calculating the cost of a repair of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including parts and labor, can take two or three hours.
Instead, with the support of the latest IT tools it would be a matter of minutes
For this reason, almost 100% of the experts use this type of system.
The providers of services and solutions for claims assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information provided by the manufacturers, and then preparing it and offering it to their clients in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, from the North American group Solera, is the leading firm; 80% of the evaluations are made with their products.
The other firms that compete in the field of appraisal tools and the preparation of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with data supplied by manufacturers is far from easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, in Spain they work with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them supplies them with information in different formats.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and engines have been launched than in the previous fifteen.
As soon as a new car hits the market, these companies go to work.
It is a very arduous task, because each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle must be cataloged and its price entered.
In addition, a &quot;smart&quot; graphic image is made of each model where different parts of the car can be &quot;punctured&quot;.
If it is a massive sale model, the job can be done in a week if the process goes too fast.
If it is a minority car, it may take three to four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models they have information about Porsche, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile fleet that circulates, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the documentation work and the elaboration of the databases, Audatex has eight centers around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized on specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanical experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros annually in developing these databases.
2.5 million pieces of data are included each month, and customers receive updates every other day.
The elaboration of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and offer various products.
The most frequent use is focused on repair and maintenance, but depending on which countries there are also tools for managing scrap parts or for calculating the sale or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that provides information on the value of used vehicles in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but it does in the United States.
In view of the products that Audatex offers, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support they can provide to professionals in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, the flagship product being AudaPlus, the standard claims valuation solution for experts.
Includes cars, motorcycles, and light or heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the paint scales.
This tool is paid according to use, for each valuation.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for clients who use it little, a maximum of ten times a month.
Afterwards, each insurance company, which performs thousands of appraisals, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the total identification of a vehicle and the equipment with which it left the assembly line only with its VIN number.
AudaGlass focuses on vehicle windows, and AudaSubastas is a service open to the professional sector on the internet that allows bidding on vehicles declared total loss.
Its statistics service is very useful to identify trends, perform geodemographic analysis or know the deviations by brands or models.
You can study, for example, how many models of a certain brand have passed through the workshop due to breakdowns or how many have suffered serious accidents in a certain period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tool.
It sells, among others, Gt Estimate, which is also intended for experts and also provides digital images, access to parts or official manufacturer prices and times.
Gt Motive is a company of the Einsa group founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of damages, breakdowns or car maintenance
The Gt Valuation Guide is your historical reference product in the market.
They work with 24,000 users in workshops, 3,100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Their business volume has grown at an annual rate of 20% in the last three years, and in 2008 they had a turnover of 10.8 million euros.
At the beginning of last year they began their internationalization process, with the installation of an office in Paris.
For its part, Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and in 1979 it was established in Spain.
According to company sources, 62% of its business is generated in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38%, in North and South America. They work with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 workshops, 3,000 of them in Spain.
